{"name": "dynamicalsystem-halogen", "metadata": {"name": "dynamicalsystem-halogen", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["python-dotenv", "requests"], "summary": "Shared library from dynamicalsystem", "upload_time": 1733771073}, "documentation": ["# Halogen\n\nHalogen contains common objects and functions for dynamicalsystem projects:\n\n## Config\n\n`dynamicalsystem.halogen.config` provides a single instance immutable object which will provide a project's config given a name (typically `__name__`) in the presence of two environment variables:\n\n- `DYNAMICAL_SYSTEM_FOLDER` - a path to the config folders\n- `DYNAMICAL_SYSTEM_ENVIRONMENT` - the environment which the config applies to (dev, test, prod, e.g.)\n\n## Utils\n\n`dynamicalsystem.halogen.utils` provides common functions which do fun stuff like:\n\n- `url_join` which jangs some `/`s into the right places given some url fragments as a string and a list of strings.\n- `cli_hyperlink` which creates a hyperlink which will display on the cli.\n- `possessive` which turns a provided noun into the possessive form in English.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "dynamicalsystem.halogen", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.config_instance", "xref": {"fqname": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.config.config_instance", "project": null}}, {"name": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.create_logger", "xref": {"fqname": "dynamicalsystem.halogen.loggin